<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FFBAFFF0A7ADF8DDFAE5DBE9" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FFBAFFF0A7ADF8DDFEF0DB4D" blockId="35.[189,310,1842,1868]" box="[189,310,1842,1868]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<heading id="5C1D150FFFBAFFF0A7ADF8DDFEF0DB4D" bold="true" box="[189,310,1842,1868]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFBAFFF0A7ADF8DDFEF0DB4D" bold="true" box="[189,310,1842,1868]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FFBAFFF0A7ADF88DFAE5DBE9" blockId="35.[189,1400,1890,2025]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
This species may be separated from other Caribbean and Central American 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFBAFFF0A353F88DFB76DB7D" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[1091,1200,1890,1916]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFBAFFF0A353F88DFB76DB7D" box="[1091,1200,1890,1916]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by means of the following combination of characters: median eyes and ocular tubercle absent; cheliceral claw with four teeth, bifid tooth of basal cheliceral segment with dorsal and ventral cusps of equal size; leg tibia I with 23 articles; tarsus I with 41 articles; first article of tarsus 1.4–1.9 times as long as second article.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
